[[File:Dariusz-karlowicz.jpg|thumb|Dariusz Karłowicz]] '''Dariusz Karłowicz''' (born 1964) is a Polish philosopher, university lecturer, columnist, and a book publisher. The president of the St. Nicolas Foundation (Fundacja Świętego Mikołaja)<ref>{{cite web|title=Historia » Fundacja Świętego Mikołaja|url=http://www.mikolaj.org.pl.|website=Fundacja Świętego Mikołaja|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref> which is an NGO involved in charitable, educational, and scientific activity. An Editor-in-chief of the Polish philosophical magazine "Political Theology" ("Teologia Polityczna")<ref>{{cite web|title=Dariusz Karłowicz|url=http://www.teologiapolityczna.pl/dariusz-karlowicz-2|website=Teologia Polityczna|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref> which analyzes the connections and relationships between philosophy, religion, and politics. Lecturer in political philosophy at the War Studies University in Warsaw. Co-author of a weekly television program "Trzeci Punkt Widzenia" on the channel TVP Kultura (on the public television). A regular columnist in the weekly Sieci (one of the largest weekly magazines in Poland).<ref>{{cite web|title=Dariusz Karłowicz felietonistą Tygodnika wSieci!|url=http://www.teologiapolityczna.pl/dariusz-karlowicz-felietonista-tygodnika-wsieci|website=Teologia Polityczna}}</ref> A member of the policy council for the magazine First Things – the Polish edition (2006-2008), The author of books and articles. The winner of the Andrzej Kijowski Prize for the book "Koniec snu Konstantyna" (2005).<ref>{{cite news|title=Karłowicz laureatem nagrody im. Kijowskiego|url=https://www.onet.pl/?srcc=ucs&pid=78b65f55-3a16-4df5-9e1f-902e04cf0c34&sid=b177a2c9-166f-4113-9b28-185bbe554807|accessdate=18 May 2018|agency=Onet Wiadomości|date=26 July 2013}}</ref> Was awarded by the Order of Polonia Restituta for charity work (2012).<ref>{{cite web|title=Ordery Polonia Restituta przyznane|url=http://www.teologiapolityczna.pl/ordery-polonia-restituta-przyznane-2|website=Teologia Polityczna|accessdate=18 May 2018|language=pl-PL}}</ref>
Books translated into English:
* ''The Archparadox of Death. Martyrdom as a philosophical category'', Polish edition published by Znak, Kraków 2000, and by Fronda, Warszawa 2007, English edition published by Peter Lang, Frankfurt 2016. * ''Socrates and Other Saints'', published by Fronda, Warszawa 2005, English edition published by Cascade Books, Wipf and Stock Publishers, Eugene, Oregon 2017.
