'''Gustav Glogau''' (6 June 1844, [[Laukischken]] (Kreis [[Labiau]], [[Ostpreußen]]) - 22 March 1895, [[Laurion]] ([[Greece]])) is a [[Germany|German]] [[philosopher of religion]]. He taught as a [[professor]] at the [[Halle University]] (1883-), [[Kiel University]] (1884-).

The name is sometime misspelled as ''Gustav Grogau''.

==Literary works==
* ''Abriss der philosophischen Grundwissenschaften'', 2 vols., 1880-1888

